# Building the macOS DMG

To produce a distributable `.dmg` installer:

```bash
bun run build:dmg   # = tauri build --bundles dmg
```

- `beforeBuildCommand` runs `bun run build` (`tsc && vite build`) automatically.
- This is a release build (Rust compiled in release mode) and can take several
  minutes; run it in the background and check on it rather than blocking.
- Output path (version/arch come from `package.json` + host CPU):

```
src-tauri/target/release/bundle/dmg/opcode_<version>_<arch>.dmg
```

  e.g. `src-tauri/target/release/bundle/dmg/opcode_0.2.1_aarch64.dmg` on Apple Silicon.

# Running / testing in dev (with HMR)

`tauri dev` is wired to run the Vite dev server (`beforeDevCommand: npm run dev`,
`devUrl: http://localhost:1420`) instead of loading the prebuilt `dist/`:

```bash
bun run tauri dev
```

What this means when prompting the user to test:

- **Frontend changes (`src/**`, TS/TSX/CSS) hot-reload instantly** — no manual
  rebuild or app restart needed. Tell the user they can just save and look.
- **Rust changes (`src-tauri/**`) require a restart** of `tauri dev` (Tauri
  recompiles the backend), not just an HMR refresh.

When you finish a frontend change, prompt the user to verify in their already-running
`tauri dev` window (changes should appear immediately). Only ask them to restart
`tauri dev` if you touched Rust code. Do not ask them to rebuild the DMG just to test.
